        <p>
            <span class="dropcap"> H </span> I would like to tell you about an eventful day in Brisbane.
            The night at the petrol station was not that bad. The rain stopped at some point. It was still quite cloudy but warm during the day. </p>
        <p> It started today with the visit to the workshop. On the way there we got the shock absorbers in an Australian version of A.T.U. While Hugo was repaired, Mutti and I went to breakfast nearby in a French caf&eacute;. That was very tasty. In the meantime we looked for a campsite near the city center of Brisbane. We want to see at least something from Brisbane after we had just stopped in Surfers Paradise yesterday. </p>
        <p> We chose the Newmarket Gardens Caravan Park. From there you come to the city center without having to change. The car was quickly repaired and the campsite was quickly found. We got one of the few free places. Most of the other campers seemed to stay here longer and had additional provisional tarpaulins against the rain of the past few days. </p>
        <p> We didn't stay long and made our way into the city. We had first decided to drive to the promenade on the Brisbane River opposite the city center. On the bus, a grandma then explained how this works with the tickets. It is similar to that in Plauen that single tickets are also valid here and you can drive back and forth as often as you want. They also apply to the ferry that drives the Brisbane River up and down. </p>

