        <p> So we decided that we almost go directly from the bus over the promenade to the ferry and drive a boat for the time being. We use the waiting time until the ferry came to look at a Nepalese pagoda and huge bamboo. This was about 5 times the size of me. What a sight. We took some photos of the skyline and of ourselves. </p>
        <p> We then drove with the modern and fast ferry as far as our tickets allowed and so that we will come back to the starting point. On the way back we decided to get out of a stop beforehand. As a result, we had arrived in the city center on the other side of the river. We then strolled through the city center and broke through some Souvenir shops and albert with Australian cowboy hats. The sun had long started when we made our way back to the campsite. </p>
