    <div class="col-md-6">
        <p> After all the fun today, we had to get serious again. Thanks to Steffi&rsquo;s help, Mutti has mastered the way to Australia well, including the change in Dubai. On the way back, she flies from Cairns to Brisbane and then switches from national to international towards Singapore and Hamburg. You have to say that there are two different terminals or different airports here in Australia often national and international airport. So here too in Brisbane. I had agreed with Mutti that I was doing an Airport training with her here today. Explain and show every step. Shortly before her departure from Cairns, she decides whether I also get a ticket to Brisbane and then take it to international airport. </p>
        <p> No sooner said than done, we made our way to the national airport in the dark with Hugo. There we looked for the calls hall and went through the process step by step. We also tried to plan every eventuality. So what has to do nuts if she has to check her suitcases herself. Where does the shuttle bus drive to the international terminal, how often does it drive, etc. We also took the bus over to the international terminal and searched for the check-in series for Emirates flights. We also found it. There was even an employee who smelled that we are not normal airport passengers and offered us his help. It turned out that he could even have a little German and explained the exact process in front of and behind the security check. That was really helpful. We will see in a few weeks whether mom dares to switch alone or whether I should. It currently looks confident. </p>
    </div>
